(347, 1, '2017-12-21 01:34:39', '2017-12-21 00:34:39', '<div class=\"wrapper\">\r\n<p class=\"p-1\">The Golden Age for women entrepreneurs has finally begun. The stars have aligned to help trigger the trend as robust ecosystems churn out enterprising females equipped with inspiration, know-how and funding. In recent years, the rate of women entrepreneurs has been growing at a percentage at least double that of their male counterparts. Women now make up 40 percent of new entrepreneurs in the United States — the highest percentage since 1996, according to the 2016 Kauffman Index of Startup Activity.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"p-1\">Celebrating women leading innovation in the Los Angeles County and Orange county</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p-1\">The Innovative Woman Award goal is to promote Entrepreneurship and the women leading it in all sectors. By participating, not only you get a chance to win great prizes to help take your business to the next level but you also get a chance to make a statement about women as business leaders, innovators, job creators, game changers whether it is a the local level or on a global scale.</p>\r\nChek out the timeline on our home page for more information about the calendar. But right now make sur you <a href=\"https://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/project-sign-up/\"><strong>Submit your project</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-344\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/climate-kic-350836-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"785\" height=\"523\" />\r\n\r\n</div>', 'The Innovative Woman Awards', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '222-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-21 01:34:39', '2017-12-21 00:34:39', '', 222, 'http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/2017/12/21/222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
