(372, 1, '2017-12-21 23:26:15', '2017-12-21 22:26:15', '<h2 class=\"title-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"title-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-363\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/intro-1.png\" alt=\"\" />WE EMPOWER SOCIAL ENTREPRENEURS</h3>\r\n<p class=\"title-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">We believe that  underrepresented entrepreneurs don’t receive the same opportunities and resources as others. We believe that these entrepreneurs are the key to the American economy and their individual communities. Our event was founded to help grow their business. The more businesses we can grow, the greater chances they have to put a positive impact in the world.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-366\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Photo-2.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h3>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.csudh.edu/incubator/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-369 aligncenter\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/logo-incubator.png\" alt=\"\" /></a>\r\n<h3>About CSUDH Innovation Incubator</h3>\r\nOur organization was founded to help underrepresented entrepreneurs grow their business. The more businesses we can help grow, the greater chances social entrepreneurs have to put a positive impact in the world.\r\n\r\nThe new Innovation Incubator at CSUDH is an Incubator/Accelerator for startups and existing businesses. The Incubator will provide practitioner based entrepreneurial education that will “teach them what they do not know” about business and entrepreneurship.\r\n\r\nThe mentor-focused Innovation Incubator’s mission is to “empower social entrepreneurs\" by serving as a catalyst and economic engine for the South Bay region and beyond.\"\r\n\r\nWe will use <strong><em>three</em></strong> pillars for our Innovation Incubator:\r\n\r\nOur first pillar is <strong>Coaching. </strong> We will <strong>coach</strong> our clients by providing both Primary Mentors and Secondary Specialist mentors to provide one-on-one advisement to help our clients grow their businesses<strong>. ALL clients must be coachable</strong>, otherwise they will be told that <em>‘we cannot help them”</em> as part of our exit interview.  The Mentors and Clients will be paired by the Selection Committee.  Hopefully these personal relationships will be very successful and become known as our secret sauce to our Innovation Incubator program.\r\n\r\nOur second pillar is <strong>Collaboration. </strong> We will foster <strong>collaboration</strong> during monthly Client Collaboration (Best Practices) meetings.  Clients will share their success and failures for the past 30 days and their plan and goals for the next 30 days during this meeting.  Occasionally, guest speakers will also participate periodically to offer educational tips.  Collaboration of like-minded entrepreneurs is oftentimes the most rewarding of the entire incubator experience. <em>We will foster that entrepreneurship is a team sport.</em>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-370\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/photo-3.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-medium\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/logo-tudigo-250x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"150\" />About Tudigo</h3>\r\nTudigo is a local crowdfunding platform that connects local businesses with local investors with Funding , Local visibility , Business community creation.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'WHO WE ARE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-21 23:26:15', '2017-12-21 22:26:15', '', 220, 'http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/2017/12/21/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
